        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-05-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-05-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="910" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d910">
                <head>Bollingen Reading Society</head>
                <note rend="inline" rendition="#center" type="source">[Translation.]</note>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bollingen</hi>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-05-07">
                        <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 7, 1865</date>.</dateline>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Editor</hi>: The Bollingen Reading Society,
                        consisting of twenty members, at an ordinary meeting last evening, resolved
                        to join in the address of sympathy and condolence to the United States of
                        North America on account of the assassination of their excellent President,
                        Abraham Lincoln, and to rejoice with them in their victories for the triumph
                        of humanity by the abolition of slavery.</p>
                <p>Respectfully, in the name of the Society,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <list>
                            <item>SOLOMON FLUKIGER, <lb/>
                                <hi rend="italic">President</hi>.</item>
                            <item>JOHN MUHLETHALER, <lb/>
                                <hi rend="italic">Actuary</hi>.</item>
                        </list>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
